ğŸ‘ Construct vector search queries

Just as you did in the previous step, you can explore the search results using an aggregation pipeline.

Querying with the aggregation builderâ€‹

Using the aggregation builder, or the MongoDB Shell, you can construct a pipeline that uses the $vectorSearch stage to query the vectorsearch index.

Add the following code for the $vectorSearch stage. Repo

public async searchBooks(query: string): Promise<Book[]> {
  const aggregationPipeline = [
    {
      $vectorSearch: {
        queryVector:  "vector goes here",
        path: "embeddings",
        numCandidates: 100,       // Number of nearest neighbors to use during the search.
        index: "vectorsearch",
        limit: 100,               // Number of documents to return in the results. Value can't exceed the value of numCandidates.
      }
    }
  ];

  const books = await collections?.books?.aggregate(aggregationPipeline).toArray() as Book[];
  return books;
}

For now, this stage will break. You will need to pass it a vector in the vector property.

Paste the following vector to replace the vector goes here text. Choose the one from the embeddings provider you imported your data before.
